Author:
Vol / Page:  6
Edition:
Quote:  I think that taxation should occur in proportion to the amount of unimproved land a man possesses - thus 5s per acre is not too great a tax on the property which carries blue tussock and wild Irishman, while 6d per acre is sufficient for the paddock carrying four sheep to the acre per annum, laid down with Poverty Bay rye grass.
